		<div id="comment_body_65088187"><p>CA dept of insurance regulates this.  It sets prices, practices and coverage requirements.  It's not really a free market, so the limitations make it impossible to offer insurances that would otherwise be available.</p><p>The first approximation of a fix should be to abolish the department, but a better solution might be to create something like a set of standards for coverage verbiage to make it possible to commoditize offerings and make products comparable.  All other limitations should probably be removed.  A f<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65088187">

</div>
</div>

